{"id":740,"date":"2019-10-02T10:25:47","date_gmt":"2019-10-02T10:25:47","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.aryausa.com\/blog\/?p=740"},"modified":"2021-07-12T13:28:34","modified_gmt":"2021-07-12T13:28:34","slug":"role-of-ai-in-iot-revolution","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.aryausa.com\/blog\/role-of-ai-in-iot-revolution","title":{"rendered":"What are the Roles of AI in the IoT Revolution?"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The rapid growth of the Internet of things has caused reliability, compatibility, and effectiveness in the IT industry in several ways. IoT is undoubtedly the next big thing in technology and has a core relationship with Artificial intelligence.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">AI is expected to perform several intelligent tasks (like speech recognition, decision-making, language understanding, etc.). It is believed to perform tasks that were earlier limited to human intelligence.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">On the other hand, the Internet of Things (IoT) refers to devices that are interrelated and transfer data over a network. IoT devices do not require a computer or human interaction devices and are already made a debut in daily lifestyle products across the world. IoT devices rely heavily on Internet connectivity.<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What is Artificial Intelligence (AI)<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Artificial_intelligence_of_things\">Artificial Intelligence<\/a> (AI) is an offshoot of computer science that studies intelligent systems (i.e. software, computers, robots, etc.). Alternatively, it can be defined as &#8220;the study and design of intelligent agents&#8221; where an intelligent agent is a system that perceives its environment and takes actions that maximize its chances of success.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Why Artificial Intelligence (AI)\u00a0<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Today, the amount of data that is generated, by both humans and machines, far outpaces humans\u2019 ability to absorb, interpret, and make complex decisions based on that data. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.aryausa.com\/blog\/artificial-intelligence-and-its-challenges-with-solution\">Artificial intelligence<\/a> forms the basis for all computer learning and is the future of all complex decision-making.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">What is the Internet of Things (IoT)<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The term &#8220;Internet of Things&#8221; has come to describe a series of technologies and research disciplines that allow the Internet to reach the real world of physical objects. Technologies such as RFID, short-range wireless communications, real-time location, and sensor networks are now becoming increasingly common, bringing the Internet of Things to commercial use. They foreshadow an exciting future that closely intertwines the physical world and cyberspace, a development that is not only relevant for researchers but also companies and individuals.<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Why the Internet of Things (IoT)<\/span><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Although the initial stages of the development of the Internet have profound implications for the technology industry, the implications of the <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.aryausa.com\/Iot-solution\">IoT Automation Solutions<\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> (IoT) will prove to be of greater scope since, due to their inherent characteristics, it is a movement that we believe will be more beyond technology to impact all industries.\u00a0<\/span><\/p>\n<h2><b>Artificial Intelligence Plays an Important Role In IoT Revolution<\/b><\/h2>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">There is a clear cross between the Internet of Things (IoT) and Artificial Intelligence (AI). IoT is about connecting machines and making use of the data generated from those machines. AI is about simulating intelligent behavior on machines of all kinds. An overlay.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">IoT allows the flow of data between devices and AI can help to make sense of this data. AI is expected to be the key propellant to the growth of the IoT revolution and take it to a new level.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Data is only useful if you create an action. To make the data processable, they must be complemented with context and creativity. The <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.aryausa.com\/get-in-touch\">AI \u200b\u200b, ML, and IoT<\/a><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> are in this context, that is, &#8216;connected intelligence&#8217; and not just connected devices.<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Do you want to leverage IoT and AI for your business? Consult with us and get the solution at\u00a0 <\/span><a id=\"info-email\" href=\"mailto:info@aryausa.com\">sales@aryausa.com<\/a><\/p>\n<p><script type=\"application\/ld+json\">\n{\n  \"@context\": \"https:\/\/schema.org\",\n  \"@type\": \"BlogPosting\",\n  \"mainEntityOfPage\": {\n    \"@type\": \"WebPage\",\n    \"@id\": \"https:\/\/www.aryausa.com\/blog\/role-of-ai-in-iot-revolution\"\n  },\n  \"headline\": \"What are the Roles of AI in the IoT Revolution?\",\n  \"description\": \"IoT devices do not require a computer or human interaction devices and are already made a debut in daily lifestyle products across the world.\",\n  \"image\": \"https:\/\/www.aryausa.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2019\/10\/2656577-1024x576-1.png\",  \n  \"author\": {\n    \"@type\": \"Organization\",\n    \"name\": \"Aryavrat Infotech Inc.\"\n  },  \n  \"publisher\": {\n    \"@type\": \"Organization\",\n    \"name\": \"Aryavrat Infotech Inc.\",\n    \"logo\": {\n      \"@type\": \"ImageObject\",\n      \"url\": \"https:\/\/www.aryausa.com\/images\/arya-logo.png\"\